The .NET CLI expects:
    A project folder (.csproj)
    Default file: Program.cs

For YOU (C++ mindset)
    Think like:
    .csproj = like CMakeLists.txt
    .cs files = like .cpp files

Common .csproj naming conventions
Match project folder name (BEST practice)
    AddApp/
    ├── AddApp.csproj
    ├── main.cs

    ✔ Most common
    ✔ Clean & professional
    ✔ Same idea as CMake project name

For build and run the project
    $dotnet build 
    $dotnet run    